ProtoDefines:
. "The \term{greatest common divisor} of $a$ and $b$ is defined
   as $$ \gcd(a,b)=\max\left\{d\in \mathbf{Z} : d \mid a and 
   d\mid b\right\}, $$ unless both $a$ and $b$ are $0$ in which
   case $\gcd(0,0)=0$."
